==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quadrennial
<hw>Quad*ren"ni*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>quadriennium</ets> a space of four years; <ets>quattuor</ets> four
+ <ets>annus</ets> year; cf. L. <ets>quadriennis</ets>. See
<er>Quadrate</er>, and <er>Annual</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Comprising four years; <as>as, a <ex>quadrennial</ex>
period</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Occurring once in four years, or at the end of every
four years; <as>as, <ex>quadrennial</ex> games</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quadrennially</ent>⟦br⟧
